<paragraph id="FA73E157411EE91A6B9DD592FC9C2674" blockId="54.[151,1436,151,1511]" box="[199,843,1018,1043]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="C8B83D45411EE91A6B9DD592FE302675" bold="true" box="[199,487,1018,1043]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Geographic distribution</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry id="82DBA1C7411EE91A6AAFD592FD9D2674" box="[501,586,1018,1042]" name="Austria" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Austria</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="82DBA1C7411EE91A690CD592FD0B2674" box="[598,732,1018,1042]" name="Switzerland" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="62F7FDD2411EE91A69B1D592FCE92674" box="[747,830,1018,1042]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="46.[151,250,1079,1102]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,409,1058]" captionTargetId="figure-559@46.[151,1436,409,1058]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 19. Records of three West Palearctic, subalpine Xyela species, X. helvetica (2 specimens from 2 collection sites), X. obscura (221 specimens from 30 collection sites) and X. uncinatae (48 specimens from 9 collection sites) and natural distribution of the (supposed) host plants, Pinus mugo (solid line) and P. uncinata (dashed line, distribution of both pines according to Meusel et al. 1965). The distribution ranges of these pine species overlap in the Alps (see text). Additional literature record included for X. obscura from the Ukraine (Zombori &amp; Ermolenko 1999)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261360" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5261360/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B2D6B2DC411EE91A6B9DD277FC642781" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FA73E157411EE91A6B9DD277FD39263C" blockId="54.[151,1436,151,1511]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="C8B83D45411EE91A6B9DD277FEE32651" bold="true" box="[199,308,1055,1079]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Remarks</emphasis>
. Females are distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD4411EE91A69F7D277FC9D2651" authorityName=", Dalman" authorityYear="1819" box="[685,842,1055,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longula">
<emphasis id="C8B83D45411EE91A69F7D277FC9D2651" box="[685,842,1055,1079]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Xyela longula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shorter ovipositor and the almost evenly pale colored valvula 1. See also remarks under 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD4411EE91A6929D22BFD3F263D" authorityName=", Dalman" authorityYear="1819" box="[627,744,1091,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longula">
<emphasis id="C8B83D45411EE91A6929D22BFD3F263D" box="[627,744,1091,1115]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">X. longula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA73E157411EE91A6B9DD20FFB432754" blockId="54.[151,1436,151,1511]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
The male of 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD4411EE91A6A0DD200FE0B2619" baseAuthorityName="Benson" baseAuthorityYear="1961" box="[343,476,1127,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helvetica">
<emphasis id="C8B83D45411EE91A6A0DD200FE0B2619" box="[343,476,1127,1151]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">X. helvetica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains unknown. The supposal of 
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA6411EE91A682DD20FFBE22619" author="Viitasaari, M." box="[887,1077,1127,1151]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="113 - 116" refId="ref72690" refString="Viitasaari, M. (1980) The taxonomy and synonymy of some eastern Fennoscandian sawfly species (Hymenoptera, Symphyta). Notulae Entomologicae, 60 (3), 113 - 116." type="journal article" year="1980">Viitasaari (1980)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA6411EE91A6F37D20FFAD52619" author="Blank, S. M." box="[1133,1282,1127,1151]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="197 - 233" refId="ref66820" refString="Blank, S. M. (2002) The Western Palaearctic Xyelidae (Hymenoptera). In: Viitasaari, M. (ed.) Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. A review of the suborder, the Western Palaearctic taxa of Xyeloidea and Pamphilioidea. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 197 - 233." type="book chapter" year="2002">Blank (2002)</bibRefCitation>
that the male reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA6411EE91A6A7AD2E2FE6826C4" author="Schedl, W." box="[288,447,1162,1186]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="97 - 115" refId="ref70996" refString="Schedl, W. (1978) Die Xyelidae Europas (Insecta: Hymenoptera, Symphyta, Xyelidae) mit besonderer Berucksichtigung der Fundnachweise aus den Ostalpen. Berichte des Naturwissenschaftlich-Medizinischen Vereins in Innsbruck, 65, 97 - 115." type="journal article" year="1978">Schedl (1978)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD4411EE91A6ABDD2E3FD8A26C5" authorityName=", Dalman" authorityYear="1819" box="[487,605,1163,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longula">
<emphasis id="C8B83D45411EE91A6ABDD2E3FD8A26C5" box="[487,605,1163,1187]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">X. longula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Hohe Wand (
<collectingRegion id="38082FB5411EE91A6863D2E2FC3526C4" box="[825,994,1162,1186]" country="Austria" name="Niederoesterreich" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Lower Austria</collectingRegion>
, NMW) belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD4411EE91A6F9ED2E3FA9E26C5" baseAuthorityName="Benson" baseAuthorityYear="1961" box="[1220,1353,1163,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helvetica">
<emphasis id="C8B83D45411EE91A6F9ED2E3FA9E26C5" box="[1220,1353,1163,1187]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">X. helvetica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be confirmed here. In this male the valviceps is quite shallowly excised on its lower edge and the tip of the longer flagellum reaches 0.85 of the width of the distal lobe. However, study of a longer series of 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD4411EE91A6FFFD2BBFB2C268D" authorityName=", Dalman" authorityYear="1819" box="[1189,1275,1235,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longula">
<emphasis id="C8B83D45411EE91A6FFFD2BBFB2C268D" box="[1189,1275,1235,1259]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">longula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males reveals now that the morphological features of this specimen fall within the variability of 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD4411EE91A6F02D290FB182769" authorityName=", Dalman" authorityYear="1819" box="[1112,1231,1271,1295]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longula">
<emphasis id="C8B83D45411EE91A6F02D290FB182769" box="[1112,1231,1271,1295]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">X. longula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thus the former identification of 
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA6411EE91A6A0BD372FE382754" author="Schedl, W." box="[337,495,1306,1330]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="97 - 115" refId="ref70996" refString="Schedl, W. (1978) Die Xyelidae Europas (Insecta: Hymenoptera, Symphyta, Xyelidae) mit besonderer Berucksichtigung der Fundnachweise aus den Ostalpen. Berichte des Naturwissenschaftlich-Medizinischen Vereins in Innsbruck, 65, 97 - 115." type="journal article" year="1978">Schedl (1978)</bibRefCitation>
was correct, and the male 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD4411EE91A6841D373FC482755" baseAuthorityName="Benson" baseAuthorityYear="1961" box="[795,927,1307,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helvetica">
<emphasis id="C8B83D45411EE91A6841D373FC482755" box="[795,927,1307,1331]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">X. helvetica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains undescribed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA73E157411EE91A6B9DD357FC642781" blockId="54.[151,1436,151,1511]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
The collection data of the only two known females indicate an occurrence in the subalpine zone of the Alps and accordingly 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD4411EE91A6A0BD30BFE02271C" authorityName="Turra (Liston" authorityYear="1995" box="[337,469,1379,1402]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mugo">
<emphasis id="C8B83D45411EE91A6A0BD30BFE02271C" box="[337,469,1379,1402]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Pinus mugo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the supposedly only larval host plant. The 
<typeStatus id="25775FF5411EE91A6889D30AFBE2271C" box="[979,1077,1378,1402]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">holotype</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingCountry id="82DBA1C7411EE91A6F22D30AFB29271C" box="[1144,1278,1378,1402]" name="Switzerland" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
was collected at 
<quantity id="3D344CB2411EE91A6BE9D3EFFEC727F8" box="[179,272,1415,1439]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" unit="m" value="1900.0">1,900 m</quantity>
altitude, and a specimen from the Haller Zunderkopf (Karwendel Mountains, 
<collectingCountry id="82DBA1C7411EE91A6FDFD3EFFB0E27F9" box="[1157,1241,1415,1439]" name="Austria" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Austria</collectingCountry>
) was swept from 
<emphasis id="C8B83D45411EE91A6BCDD3C3FE6427A5" box="[151,435,1451,1475]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD4411EE91A6BCDD3C3FF2127A4" authorityName="Turra (Liston" authorityYear="1995" box="[151,246,1451,1474]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mugo">P. mugo</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD4411EE91A6A58D3C3FE6427A5" box="[258,435,1451,1475]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sylvestris">Pinus sylvestris</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, which was additionally taken into consideration (
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA6411EE91A68A9D3C2FB5227A4" author="Schedl, W." box="[1011,1157,1450,1474]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="97 - 115" refId="ref70996" refString="Schedl, W. (1978) Die Xyelidae Europas (Insecta: Hymenoptera, Symphyta, Xyelidae) mit besonderer Berucksichtigung der Fundnachweise aus den Ostalpen. Berichte des Naturwissenschaftlich-Medizinischen Vereins in Innsbruck, 65, 97 - 115." type="journal article" year="1978">Schedl 1978</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="9E5D9CA6411EE91A6FCBD3C2FACE27A4" author="Blank, S. M." box="[1169,1305,1450,1474]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="197 - 233" refId="ref66820" refString="Blank, S. M. (2002) The Western Palaearctic Xyelidae (Hymenoptera). In: Viitasaari, M. (ed.) Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. A review of the suborder, the Western Palaearctic taxa of Xyeloidea and Pamphilioidea. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 197 - 233." type="book chapter" year="2002">Blank 2002</bibRefCitation>
), should be excluded, because it is absent in the subalpine zone of the central Alps.
</paragraph>
